               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18400406-name-416" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18400406-name-416" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18400406-name-416" type="surname" value="PAINTER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18400406-name-416" type="given" value="RICHARD"></interp>RICHARD PAINTER</persName>
                  </hi>. I was in the employ of Thomas and William Vesper, pawnbrokers. On the 10th of March this waistcoat was on the top of some beds outside the door—about four o'clock in the afternoon I received information, went out, and found the prisoner under an arch in Lucas-street, with this waistcoat.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. PHILLIPS</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> How long after you lost it did you find it? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> About five minutes—I pulled her cloak on one side, and saw it—she said she picked it up—she had not been in oar shop—I did not see any body take it—I was attending to somebody else at the door, who was buying articles.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
